<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="369" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1128,220,723]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,258,220,243]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BALY J. S." box="[265,392,220,243]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" refId="ref19430" refString="BALY J. S. 1859: Catalogue of Hispidae in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 172 pp. + 9 pls." type="book" year="1859">BALY (1859)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on a single specimen as he clearly indicated. Subsequently it was mentioned only in catalogues (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="WEISE J." box="[762,883,252,275]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" refId="ref20946" refString="WEISE J. 1911: Chrysomelidae: Hispinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus, Pars 35. W. Junk, Berlin, 94 pp." type="book" year="1911">WEISE 1911</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="BRYANT G. E." box="[893,1029,252,275]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" pagination="195 - 208" refId="ref19819" refString="BRYANT G. E. 1942: Lista provisional de los crisomelidos (Coleoptera) de Venezuela. Boletin de la Sociedad Venezolana de Ciencias Naturales 8: 195 - 208." type="journal article" year="1942">BRYANT 1942</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="UHMANN E." pageId="18" pageNumber="369" pagination="1 - 153" refId="ref20731" refString="UHMANN E. 1957 a: Chrysomelidae: Hispinae. Hispinae Americanae. In: HINCKS W. D. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa, Pars 35, Fasc. 1. Dr. W. Junk, 's-Gravenhage, vii + pp. 1 - 153." type="book chapter" year="1957">UHMANN 1957a</bibRefCitation>
).STAINES &amp; GARCÍA- ROBLEDO (2014) provided redescription, colour photograph and reported additional specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[417,518,316,339]" name="Colombia" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Colombia</collectingCountry>
without any further data.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1128,220,723]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">
I have studied the 
<typeStatus box="[370,460,348,371]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">holotype</typeStatus>
and in my opinion the species belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1859" box="[995,1078,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1078,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it possesses all principal characters of that genus, e.g. long antennae, serrate lateroapical margins of elytra, smooth and convex frons and vertex. Therefore I hereby transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1859" box="[874,1126,412,435]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cephaloleia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneipennis">
<emphasis box="[874,1126,412,435]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Cephaloleia aeneipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1859" box="[280,362,444,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[280,362,444,467]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1128,220,723]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[181,393,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeneipennis">
<emphasis box="[181,393,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Xenispa aeneipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1934)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[587,825,476,499]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinata">
<emphasis box="[587,704,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">X. carinata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="PIC M." box="[718,818,476,499]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" pagination="1 - 36" refId="ref20264" refString="PIC M. 1934: Nouveautes diverses, notes. Melanges Exotico-Entomologiques 63: 1 - 36." type="journal article" year="1934">Pic, 1934</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
also known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1015,1124,476,499]" name="Venezuela" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. The two species can be distinguished using the herein proposed key to Venezuelan species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,233,540,563]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Xenispa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,233,540,563]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Xenispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, see page 374.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1128,220,723]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">
I was not able to verify the identity of the specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[738,839,572,595]" name="Colombia" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">Colombia</collectingCountry>
(STAINES &amp; GARCÍA- ROBLEDO 2014) as it was not found in the collections of NHMW (Harald Schillhammer, pers. comm. 
<date pageId="18" pageNumber="369" value="2017-10">October 2017</date>
) and I doubt that the identification was correct since the authors made numerous errors in species identification. So the 
<typeStatus box="[447,537,668,691]" pageId="18" pageNumber="369">holotype</typeStatus>
remains the only specimen of this species known to me.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
